---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof for Pet Sitters & Dog Walkers — Reviews That Build Your Client List | SocialProof" description="Pet sitters and dog walkers: pet owners are protective. SocialProof helps you collect and display testimonials that show you're trustworthy before they hand over their keys.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Pet Sitters &amp; Dog Walkers
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Pet owners are trusting you with a family member and sometimes a house key. That decision doesn't happen without strong social proof. SocialProof helps you collect genuine client testimonials and display them on your website — so new clients arrive already confident they've found the right person.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why trust is everything in pet care</h2>
      <p>Pet sitting and dog walking is an intensely personal service. Clients aren't just hiring someone for a task — they're trusting someone with their pet's wellbeing and sometimes access to their home. The barrier to a first booking is high, and it drops dramatically when you have visible proof from other pet owners who love you.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;">A testimonial widget on your website — showing real words from real clients and their dogs — answers the anxiety before it even forms.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What pet owner testimonials say that converts</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Peace of mind:</strong> "She sent photo updates every few hours. I could actually relax on vacation for the first time."</li>
        <li><strong>Genuine care:</strong> "You could tell she actually loves dogs. Max was exhausted and happy every single walk."</li>
        <li><strong>Reliability:</strong> "Never missed a walk in 18 months. Always on time, always communicates."</li>
        <li><strong>Special needs:</strong> "Our senior dog needs medication twice a day — she handles it like a pro."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How it works</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li>After a pet sitting stay or a month of walks, send a SocialProof link to your client</li>
        <li>They submit a quick testimonial — and can include a photo of their pet</li>
        <li>You approve and it goes live on your website</li>
        <li>New clients find you and see a page full of happy pet owners before they send the first message</li>
      </ol>

      <div style="background:#f8f9fa;border-radius:12px;padding:2rem;margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Free forever for 1 active widget</h3>
        <p style="color:#555;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Start collecting and displaying pet care testimonials today. No credit card required.</p>
        <a href="https://socialproof.dev/signup" style="display:inline-block;background:#0070f3;color:#fff;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:8px;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">Start free</a>
      </div>

      <section style="margin-top:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
          "@context": "https://schema.org",
          "@type": "FAQPage",
          "mainEntity": [
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "How do I get more clients as a pet sitter or dog walker?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Word of mouth is powerful in pet care, but most referrals now start with a website visit. Having visible testimonials from existing clients on your website means referrals arrive already trusting you — and you can attract new clients organically from local search."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Should pet sitters use a profile on Rover or their own website?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Both — but your own website means you keep all the client relationships and aren't paying platform fees. SocialProof testimonials on your own site help you build a direct client base you own completely."
              }
            }
          ]
        })}>
        </script>

        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">How do I get more clients as a pet sitter or dog walker?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">Word of mouth is powerful, but most referrals now start with a website visit. Having visible testimonials means referrals arrive already trusting you — and you can attract new clients from local search.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">Should I use Rover or my own website?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">Both — but your own website means you keep all client relationships and don't pay platform fees. SocialProof testimonials on your own site help you build a direct client base you own completely.</p>
        </details>
      </section>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
